# Topological–Geometrical Descriptor (TGD) for 2D Carbon Systems

This repository provides an implementation of the **Topological–Geometrical Descriptor (TGD)**, a physically interpretable descriptor designed for **two-dimensional sp/sp² carbon systems**.

The TGD maps atomic structures into a compact set of **topological and geometrical observables** derived from the planar bonding graph and its ring statistics. It was developed to characterize systems such as graphene, defect-rich carbon allotropes, and porous 2D carbon networks.

The repository includes:

- `descriptor_TGD.py`: code to generate the TGD from crystal structures in `.cif` format
- `structure/`: example structural database with representative carbon systems
- an interpretability code to read the generated descriptors and create figures for structural analysis

## Repository structure

```bash
.
├── descriptor_TGD.py
├── interpretability.py
├── structure/
│   ├── graphene.cif
│   ├── phagraphene.cif
│   └── cey_graphene.cif
├── output/
│   ├── descriptors/
│   └── figures/
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
